author: Alucard_Tepes
title: 30495-1: AT-ST
review: It's decent for what it is. The parts aren't too bad. Its small size kinda looks cute compared to the much bigger one. For 7 bucks, it's not too shabby. And I feel it's a great army builder.

author: StarKiller22515
title: Hoth AT-ST Polybag
review: While not very flashy this polybag accurately represents the larger set it is based off of which is accurate to what is seen in the movie. This is a good set for what it is and is a great stocking stuffer.
